         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ […] ¶  Plagianthus pulcellus ¶  A Gray Forgive this rambling letter and believe me your much ¶ obliged ¶  ¶ F M Bailey ¶ PS Thanks for the name of the native grass it is not to be found in any of m...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">74.00.00d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M5, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">There are three Bailey specimens of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Eragrostis elongata</seg> (the modern synonym of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Poa%20interrupta">Poa interrupta</name>
                     </seg>) at MEL, all from Brisbane. The two with dates are given as March 1873, but that is inconsistent with Bailey's reference to M's <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg> where M's major treatment of the grasses is in B73.11.03 and B73.12.01; thus the earliest plausible date for this letter fragment is 1874 and it is dated accordingly.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[…]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">An unknown amount of text missing. </p>
               </note>
               <name key="Plagianthus%20pulcellus">Plagianthus pulcellus</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">P. pulchellus</seg>
                     <seg style="">?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> A Gray Forgive this rambling letter and believe me your much</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">obliged</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F M Bailey</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">PS Thanks for the name of the native grass it is not to be found in any of my books The grass is worth recommending I posted all the good seeds I could collect, to you the other day. A person brought me up from the bay<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">Moreton Bay, Qld?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> the other day what I take to be Robt Browns <name key="Poa%20interrupta">Poa interrupta</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">R. Brown (1810), 180.</p>
               </note> I'll enclose a specimen You dont seem to have noticed it in the Fragmenta so perhaps I am wrong</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">F. M. B.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Plagianthus%20pulcellus">Plagianthus pulcellus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Poa%20interrupta">Poa interrupta</name>
            </p>
